1 A BILL for an Act to provide an appropriation to the insurance commissioner for a North Dakota
2 firefighter's association grant; and to declare an emergency.
3 BE IT ENACTED BY THE LEGISLATIVE ASSEMBLY OF NORTH DAKOTA
4 SECTION 1. APPROPRIATION - STRATEGIC INVESTMENT AND IMPROVEMENTS
5 FUND - INSURANCE COMMISSIONER - NORTH DAKOTA FIREFIGHTER'S ASSOCIATION
6 GRANT - ONE-TIME FUNDING. There is appropriated out of any moneys in the strategic
7 investment and improvements fund in the state treasury, not otherwise appropriated, the sum of
8 $500,000, or so much of the sum as may be necessary, to the insurance commissioner for the
9 purpose of providing a grant to the North Dakota firefighter's association, for the period
10 beginning with the effective date of this Act, and ending June 30, 2027. Grant funds must be
11 used only to defray the costs associated with a new firefighter's association building. The
12 funding provided in this section is considered a one-time funding item.
13 SECTION 2. EMERGENCY. This Act is declared to be an emergency measure.
